# Brisart Ecosystem License

This repository serves as the central source of truth for
licensing information across the Brisart ecosystem.

Covered projects may include:

- BrisartDevTools
- BrisartResearchArchive
- BrisartPreservationTools
- BrisartIdentityTools

and future Brisart ecosystem projects unless explicitly stated otherwise.

---

## Official Releases

Official Brisart releases may be downloaded, executed,
evaluated, studied, and used according to current
ecosystem terms.

Official releases are distributed through official
Brisart-controlled repositories and distribution channels.

---

## Source Availability

Source code may be published and made available for
inspection, study, evaluation, and educational purposes.

Publication of source code does not automatically grant
all modification, redistribution, or forking rights.

Users should refer to current ecosystem policies for the
latest participation and modification terms.

---

## Modification Rights

Organizations and individuals participating in an active
Brisart ecosystem subscription program may maintain private
modified versions of Brisart software for internal use.

Such modifications may include:

- Workflow customization
- Internal feature additions
- Internal integrations
- Environment-specific changes
- Research-specific adaptations

Modified versions must remain private unless explicitly
authorized otherwise.

---

## Subscription-Based Modification Use

The right to create and use private modified versions is an
ecosystem participation benefit.

If participation in the applicable subscription program
ends, modification rights granted through that program
terminate.

Former subscribers may continue using official releases
according to current ecosystem terms.

Use of modified versions created under subscription-based
modification rights may require reactivation of an active
subscription before continued use.

---

## Forking

Forking, modification, and derivative development may be
subject to current ecosystem participation policies.

Users should refer to current Brisart ecosystem policies
for the latest applicable terms.

---

## Redistribution

Redistribution rights, publication rights, and related
permissions may be governed by current ecosystem policies.

Users should refer to the BrisartLicensing repository for
current information.

---

## Updates

Licensing terms, participation programs, ecosystem
policies, and related documentation may change over time.

Users should refer to this repository for the latest
available ecosystem-wide information.

---

## Questions

Questions regarding:

- Use of Brisart software
- Modification rights
- Forking rights
- Ecosystem participation
- Subscription programs
- Redistribution
- Donations
- Implementation requests

should be directed to the BrisartLicensing repository as
the authoritative source of ecosystem information.
